### Commercial Limitation for Public Companies

Permission is granted to use this software for any purpose, including for-profit commercial use, with one specific exception:

If this software, or any work derived from it, is used in a product or service by a company that is, or becomes, publicly traded on any stock exchange (through an IPO, merger, acquisition, or any other means), then that company agrees to grant Sum1Solutions, LLC a one-time equity stake equivalent to one percent (1%) of the company's total outstanding shares as of the date of the public listing or acquisition. This equity stake may be open to negotiation with Sum1Solutions, LLC.

This grant is a precondition of the license for such use. For all other private commercial, personal, or non-profit use, this software is free to use without this condition.
